                    Since September 30, 2024 I have worked as an Administrative Assistant at LAZ Parking while
                    attending Western Washington University full time. In this role I assist with organizing
                    operational documents, maintaining records, and supporting communication between team members.
                    Working in this position gave me a better understanding of how businesses manage daily operations
                    and coordinate tasks across teams. I quickly realized how important organization and attention to
                    detail are when managing business information. Balancing work with a full academic schedule also
                    required strong time management and prioritization skills. I enjoyed gaining real workplace
                    experience while continuing my education. This role helped me develop stronger communication,
                    responsibility, and professional work habits. In my future career I will apply these skills when
                    working in professional environments that require organization, teamwork, and accountability.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

