                <div class="card-date">November 25, 2023</div>
                <p class="card-reflection">
                    On November 25, 2023 I created and began actively using my LinkedIn account to build a
                    professional online presence. After creating the account I spent time developing my profile by
                    adding my education, work experience, and skills related to business and technology. I also
                    connected with classmates, professors, and professionals in industries I am interested in.
                    Exploring other professionals' profiles helped me learn about different career paths and
                    understand what skills employers value. I enjoyed seeing how people present their accomplishments
                    and experiences in a professional format. This helped me think more intentionally about how I
                    communicate my own skills and experiences. Maintaining a LinkedIn profile helped strengthen my
                    professional networking skills. In my future career I plan to continue using LinkedIn to build
                    connections and stay informed about opportunities in my field.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="activity-card-v2">
            <div class="card-image-wrap career-bar">
                <img src="~/files/handshake.jpg" alt="Handshake" onerror="this.closest('.card-image-wrap').classList.add('img-error')" />
                <div class="card-img-placeholder"><span>Add Photo</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <div class="card-header-row">
                    <span class="card-title">Handshake Career Services Account</span>
                    <span class="card-badge career-badge">1 pt</span>
                </div>
                <div class="card-date">November 10, 2023</div>
                <p class="card-reflection">
                    On November 10, 2023 I created an account on Handshake through Western Washington University
                    Career Services. Handshake is a platform that connects students with internships, job
                    opportunities, and employer networking events. After signing up I explored different job postings
                    and reviewed employer profiles to understand what skills companies are seeking. I also looked at
                    internship opportunities related to business and technology fields. Using the platform helped me
                    connect what I was learning in my courses with real career opportunities after graduation. I
                    appreciated how easy it was to access job listings specifically targeted toward students and
                    recent graduates. The platform encouraged me to begin thinking seriously about career preparation
                    and professional opportunities. In the future I will continue using resources like Handshake to
                    find internships, connect with employers, and develop my career path.
                </p>
